docs.abstract: The online retail giant is taking advantage of what it knows better than anyone: consumers’ online shopping habits.

docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — When a chain of physical therapy centers wanted new patients, it aimed online ads at people near its offices who had bought knee braces recently on Amazon.

headline.main: Amazon Knows What You Buy. And It’s Building a Big Ad Business From It.

docs.abstract: With a little time, typing and easy-to-use software, you can quickly see your financial picture much more thoroughly and better plan for the future.
docs.snippet: With a little time, typing and easy-to-use software, you can quickly see your financial picture much more thoroughly and better plan for the future.
docs.lead_paragraph: It’s January and you’ve gone and done it: You’ve resolved to keep better track of your personal finances. But deep down, you’re not sure where to start. Sure, you can buy accounting software, sign up for a service or poke around your bank’s online offerings for money management. But don’t overlook what is probably the best option of all: a simple and free spreadsheet you make yourself.

headline.main: The Easy (and Free) Way to Make a Budget Spreadsheet
headline.print_headline: Need a Budget? Ways to Follow Your Money

docs.abstract: The Vanguard Group founder set up his firm so investors in its mutual funds would own it. While business titans are often measured by the size of their assets, he said, “I don’t share those values.”
docs.snippet: The Vanguard Group founder set up his firm so investors in its mutual funds would own it. While business titans are often measured by the size of their assets, he said, “I don’t share those values.”
docs.lead_paragraph: In the summer of 2012, I called John C. Bogle to discuss his favorite subject: index funds and the plight of rank-and-file investors. He had urged me to reach out to him “anytime I needed him,” and I took him up on that offer regularly.

headline.main: Vanguard’s Jack Bogle Wasn’t a Billionaire. He Was Proud of That.

docs.abstract: In addition to moving away from newsstands, the publication is laying off roughly 30 percent of its staff, including the editor in chief, Jane Eisner.
docs.snippet: In addition to moving away from newsstands, the publication is laying off roughly 30 percent of its staff, including the editor in chief, Jane Eisner.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Forward, the 121-year-old Jewish publication that started as a Yiddish-language daily newspaper for those who had fled persecution in Europe, announced on Thursday that it planned to stop publishing print editions this spring.

headline.main: In Print Since 1897, The Forward Goes Digital Only
headline.print_headline: Printed Since 1897, Forward Plans to Publish Online Only

docs.abstract: Flu season is here, and there are at least six types of vaccine to choose from. It’s worth studying the options to determine which is likely to protect you the most.
docs.snippet: Flu season is here, and there are at least six types of vaccine to choose from. It’s worth studying the options to determine which is likely to protect you the most.
docs.lead_paragraph: When I went to a pharmacy in Brooklyn to get a flu shot last year, I was presented with a choice: one vaccine with three different strains of the flu virus for about $30 or, for just $10 more, four strains. It sounded vaguely like a late-night television infomercial.

headline.main: What to Know About Getting a Flu Shot This Year, No Matter Who’s Paying
headline.print_headline: Which Shot Should I Get For the Flu?
